The paper discusses the impact of the growth of IXPs on Internet routes, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also touches upon security concerns related to IXPs, which could fall under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). The analysis of the data and observations made in the paper could also fall under the categories of social and information networks (cs.SI) and systems and control (cs.SD). Finally, the paper discusses the evolution of the Internet over the past decade, which could fall under the category of information theory (cs.IT).
